---
import Article from "../layouts/Article.astro";
import { site } from "../data/site";

const title = "Figma Motion to code — Blinn Motion runtime";
const description =
  "Export Figma Motion to production code with Blinn Motion. MotionDoc JSON + pure-JS engine for React, Vue, DOM, Canvas, and React Native — seek, scrub, identical timing.";
const path = "/figma-motion-to-code";

const howTo = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "HowTo",
  name: "Export Figma Motion to production code with Blinn Motion",
  description,
  totalTime: "PT10M",
  tool: [
    { "@type": "HowToTool", name: "Figma with Figma Motion" },
    { "@type": "HowToTool", name: "Blinn Motion Figma plugin" },
    { "@type": "HowToTool", name: "Node.js / npm" },
  ],
  step: [
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      name: "Animate in Figma Motion",
      text: "Build your timeline on a top-level frame with Figma Motion keyframes, springs, and easing.",
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      name: "Export a MotionDoc",
      text: "Run the Blinn Motion plugin, pick your framework, and download the MotionDoc JSON.",
      url: "https://docs.blinnmotion.com/guides/figma-plugin/",
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      name: "Install an adapter",
      text: "npm i @blinn-motion/react (or vue, svelte, angular, lit, dom, canvas, react-native).",
    },
    {
      "@type": "HowToStep",
      name: "Mount and play",
      text: "Pass the MotionDoc to the adapter and call play(), or drive progress 0…1 for scroll-linked motion.",
      url: "https://docs.blinnmotion.com/quickstart/",
    },
  ],
};
---

<Article
  title={title}
  description={description}
  path={path}
  eyebrow="Figma Motion → production"
  h1="Figma Motion to code with Blinn Motion"
  lead="Turn a Figma Motion timeline into a portable MotionDoc and play it with a pure-JS engine — the same motion on every platform."
  extraJsonLd={howTo}
>
  <p>
    <strong>Figma Motion</strong> lets designers author real timelines on the canvas. Shipping that motion
    into an app still means a handoff: CSS snippets, one-off React paste, video exports, or a full rebuild.
    <strong>Blinn Motion</strong> is the runtime path: export once, play everywhere.
  </p>

  <h2>Why “export from Figma” is not always enough</h2>
  <p>
    Figma’s own Dev Mode handoff can copy CSS, JSON, or framework-oriented snippets. That is useful for
    inspection and small cases. Production product UI usually needs more:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>One artifact in git</strong> — a diffable JSON file, not a screenshot of a panel</li>
    <li><strong>Seek, scrub, and shared clocks</strong> — scrubbers, storyboards, multi-view sync</li>
    <li><strong>Scroll and gesture drivers</strong> — progress 0…1, not only “press play”</li>
    <li><strong>Web and native</strong> — DOM/Canvas and React Native from the same document</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Blinn targets that gap. The Figma timeline becomes a <a href={`${site.docs}/concepts/motiondoc`}>MotionDoc</a>;
    <code>sample(doc, t)</code> in <code>@blinn-motion/core</code> is the render method; adapters only paint.
  </p>

  <h2>The pipeline</h2>
  <pre><code>Figma Motion timeline
        │  plugin export
        ▼
   MotionDoc JSON   (git-friendly)
        │  sample(doc, t)
        ▼
   pure-JS render tree
        │
        ├─ DOM / CSS / SVG
        ├─ Canvas 2D
        ├─ React · Vue · Svelte · Angular · Lit
        └─ React Native</code></pre>

  <h2>Quick path: Figma → React</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Animate a frame in <strong>Figma Motion</strong>.</li>
    <li>Open the <a href={`${site.docs}/guides/figma-plugin`}>Blinn Motion plugin</a> → Export → React → download JSON.</li>
    <li>Install: <code>npm i @blinn-motion/react</code></li>
    <li>Mount:</li>
  </ol>
  <pre><code>import &#123; BlinnMotion &#125; from "@blinn-motion/react";
import doc from "./card.motion.json";

// clock-driven
&lt;BlinnMotion doc=&#123;doc&#125; renderer="canvas" loop autoplay /&gt;

// progress-driven (scroll, drag, state)
&lt;BlinnMotion doc=&#123;doc&#125; progress=&#123;scrollP&#125; /&gt;</code></pre>
  <p>
    Full walkthrough: <a href={`${site.docs}/quickstart`}>docs quickstart</a> · live lab:
    <a href="https://react.blinnmotion.com/">react.blinnmotion.com</a>.
  </p>

  <h2>When to use Blinn vs native Figma export</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Need</th>
        <th>Figma copy/export</th>
        <th>Blinn Motion</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>One-off CSS for a marketing section</td>
        <td>Often enough</td>
        <td>Optional</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Same motion on React + RN</td>
        <td>Manual port</td>
        <td>One MotionDoc</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Scrubber / timeline UI</td>
        <td>Rebuild yourself</td>
        <td>Built-in seek / progress</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Git review of motion changes</td>
        <td>Hard</td>
        <td>Diff the JSON</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>MP4 / GIF for social</td>
        <td>Native export</td>
        <td>Not the primary path</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Related guides</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href="/vs-lottie">Blinn Motion vs Lottie</a> — payload and player size for UI motion</li>
    <li><a href="/faq">FAQ</a> — frameworks, license, scroll-driven motion</li>
    <li><a href={`${site.docs}/reference/figma-coverage`}>Figma Motion coverage</a> — what converts today</li>
    <li><a href={`${site.docs}/guides/playback`}>Playback guide</a> — play, pause, seek, rates</li>
  </ul>

  <blockquote>
    Product home: <a href="/">{site.url}</a> · Docs: <a href={site.docs}>{site.docs}</a> · MIT on
    <a href={site.repo}>GitHub</a>.
  </blockquote>
</Article>
